kubectl create deployment nginx-deployment --image=nginx
kubectl expose deployment nginx-deployment --name=nginx-svc --port=80 --target-port=8080 --type=ClusterIP
kubectl expose deployment nginx-deployment --type=NodePort --port=80
kubectl expose deployment nginx-deployment --type=NodePort --port=80 --target-port=80 --name=nginx-nodeport (lets us access svc externally)
In order to access the svc we ll have to change the network setting of our vm we will have to enable port 31215 and use node ip not svc cluster ip
